The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 New venue for NCA

Dharamsala: The Indian cricket board has decided to have an alternate venue for its National Cricket Academy (NCA) during summer and has short-listed Dharamsala and Ooty as options. 

The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) has already taken the decision and short-listed Dharamsala and Ooty as possible options, Sunil Dev, sports secretary of the Delhi and District Cricket Association and also a member of the NCA said on Sunday. (PTI) 




